1 advisory committee as the developer's representative on the committee. In addition, in a single
2 county district, the board of commissioners may make two additional appointments of such other
3 persons as the board of commissioners deems appropriate, and in a multi-county district, each
4 board of county commissioners may make one additional appointment of such other person as
5 that board of commissioners deems appropriate. Whenever a vacancy occurs on the committee
6 in a position filled by appointment by the board of commissioners, the appropriate board, before
7 filling the vacancy, shall request the association to submit the names of at least two persons to
8 be considered for the vacancy; and the board shall fill the vacancy by appointing one of the
9 persons so submitted, except that if the vacancy is in a position appointed by the board of
10 commissioners under the preceding sentence of this section, the board of commissioners making
11 that appointment shall fill the vacancy with such person as that board of commissioners deems
12 appropriate.
13 …."
14 SECTION 1.3. G.S. 153A-314 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 153A-314. Extension of service districts.
16 …
17 (a1) Multi-County Districts. – If territory that lies wholly in one county is to be annexed
18 to a multi-county district, only the board of commissioners of that county is required to adopt a
19 resolution annexing the territory. In annexing territory under this subsection, the board of
20 commissioners shall comply with the provisions of this section.
21 …."
22 SECTION 1.4. G.S. 153A-315 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 153A-315. Required provision or maintenance of services.
24 (a) New District. – When a county or counties define a research and production service
25 district, it or they shall provide, maintain, or let contracts for the services for which the district is
26 being taxed within a reasonable time, not to exceed one year, after the effective date of the
27 definition of the district. The county may designate the developer of the research and
28 development park established as a research and production service district as an agent that may
29 contract, with the approval of the county in which the research and production service district is
30 located, for the provision of services, construction, and procurement within the research and
31 production service district. The developer-agent may own property necessary to provide the
32 services, including, but not limited to, streets, sidewalks, parks, schools, utilities, and public
33 transportation systems, and proceeds of taxes levied within the research and production service
34 district used to pay for or maintain the property providing the service are presumptively expended
35 for a public purpose.
36 …."
37
38 PART II. URBAN RESEARCH SERVICE DISTRICT
39 SECTION 2.1. G.S. 153A-316.1 reads as rewritten:
40 "§ 153A-316.1. Urban research service district (URSD).
41 …
42 (a1) Multi-County Districts. – If an area that meets the standards for creation of a research
43 and production service district lies in more than one county, the boards of commissioners of those
44 counties may adopt concurrent resolutions establishing a district, even if that portion of the
45 district lying in any one of the counties does not by itself meet the standards. Each of the county
46 boards of commissioners shall follow the procedure set out in this section for creation of a district.
47 …."
48 SECTION 2.2. G.S. 153A-316.2 reads as rewritten:
49 "§ 153A-316.2. URSD advisory committee.
50 (a) Members. – The board of commissioners, in the resolution establishing a URSD, shall
51 also provide for an advisory committee for the URSD. The committee shall have at least 10
