1 members, serving whose appointments and terms as shall be set forth in the resolution. The
2 resolution shall provide for the appointment or designation of a chairperson. The board of
3 commissioners shall appoint the members of the USRD [URSD] advisory committee. In the case
4 of a multi-county URSD, the resolution may allow for the appointments to be divided among the
5 counties proportionate to the respective size of the research and production service district.
6 Before making the appointments, the board shall request the association of owners and tenants,
7 required by G.S. 153A-312(a), to submit a list of persons to be considered for appointment to the
8 committee. The association shall submit at least two names for each appointment to be made.
9 Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, the board of commissioners shall make the
10 appointments to the committee from the list of persons submitted.
11 (b) Additional Members. – In addition to the members provided in subsection (a) of this
12 section, the developer of the research and production park established as a research and
13 production service district shall appoint one person to the URSD advisory committee as the
14 developer's representative on the committee. The board of commissioners may make two
15 additional appointments of such other persons as the board of commissioners deems
16 appropriate.appropriate; provided, however, in the case of a multi-county URSD, established as
17 provided in G.S. 153A-316.1(a1), the board of commissioners of each county may make one
18 additional appointment.
19 …."
20 SECTION 2.3. G.S. 153A-316.3 reads as rewritten:
21 "§ 153A-316.3. Extension of URSD.
22 …
23 (a1) Multi-County Districts. – If territory that lies wholly in one county is to be annexed
24 to a multi-county URSD, only the board of commissioners of that county shall be required to
25 adopt a resolution annexing the territory. In annexing territory under this subsection, the board
26 of commissioners shall comply with the provisions of this section.
27 …."
28 SECTION 2.4. G.S. 153A-316.5 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 153A-316.5. Required provision or maintenance of services in URSD.
30 (a) New URSD. – When a county or counties defines a URSD, it shall provide, maintain,
31 or let contracts for the services for which the URSD is being taxed within a reasonable time, not
32 to exceed one year, after the effective date of the definition of the URSD. When a county defines
33 a URSD, it may designate the developer of the research and development park established as a
34 research and production service district in which the URSD is located as an agent that may
35 contract with any local government for the provision of services within the URSD.contract, with
36 the approval of the county or counties in which the URSD is located, for the provision of services,
37 construction, and procurement within the URSD. The developer-agent may own property
38 necessary to provide the services, including, but not limited to, streets, sidewalks, parks, schools,
39 utilities, and public transportation systems, and proceeds of taxes levied within the research and
40 production service district used to pay for or maintain the property providing the service are
41 presumptively expended for a public purpose.
42 …."
43 SECTION 2.5. G.S. 153A-317 reads as rewritten:
44 "§ 153A-317. Research and production service district taxes authorized; rate limitation.
45 (a) Tax Authorized. – A county, upon recommendation of the advisory committee
46 established pursuant to G.S. 153A-313, may levy property taxes within a research and production
47 service district in addition to those levied throughout the county, in order to finance, provide, or
48 maintain for the district services provided therein in addition to or to a greater extent than those
49 financed, provided, or maintained for the entire county. In addition, a county may allocate to a
50 district any other revenues whose use is not otherwise restricted by law. The proceeds of taxes
